        "design APIs and data models",
        "design a system",
        "evaluate architectural decisions",
        "plan for scale and reliability" ;
    oc:yieldsState oc:DocumentCreated .

oc:kn_80bb108a a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When completing any design document" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always identify what you would revisit as the system grows — flag assumptions that may become invalid at higher scale" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Systems evolve; documenting future decision points prevents costly re-architecture" .

oc:kn_84521ad2 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always — this is the expected output structure" ;
    oc:directiveContent """## {System Name} Design
### Requirements
- **Functional**: {what_it_does}
- **Non-functional**: {scale_latency_availability_cost}
- **Constraints**: {team_timeline_tech_stack}
### High-Level Design
- Component diagram
- Data flow
- API contracts
- Storage choices
### Deep Dive
- Data model
- API endpoints
- Caching / Queues / Error handling
### Scale & Reliability
- Load estimation / Scaling strategy / Failover / Monitoring
### Trade-off Analysis
- {decision} → {pros} vs {cons}
### Future Reconsiderations
- {what_to_revisit_as_system_grows}""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "System Name",
        "cons",
        "decision",
        "pros",
        "scale_latency_availability_cost",
        "team_timeline_tech_stack",
        "what_it_does",
        "what_to_revisit_as_system_grows" .

oc:kn_93bf9264 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing any system or architecture" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Gather requirements (functional, non-functional, constraints) 2. Produce high-level design (components, data flow, APIs, storage) 3. Deep dive (data model, endpoints, caching, queues, error handling) 4. Plan scale and reliability (load estimation, scaling, failover, monitoring) 5. Analyze trade-offs (complexity, cost, familiarity, time to market, maintainability)" ;
    oc:hasRationale "This sequential framework ensures no critical design dimension is overlooked" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_f9fd723b a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating any design choice" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every architectural decision has trade-offs — make them explicit and consider complexity, cost, team familiarity, time to market, and maintainability" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Implicit trade-offs lead to surprised stakeholders and unsustainable architectures" .

oc:kn_fd28349b a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before moving to high-level design phase" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Design must account for both functional and non-functional requirements before producing any component diagram or API contract" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Skipping requirements gathering leads to designs that solve the wrong problem or fail under real-world conditions" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

_:ref_0f50c8242135a50c a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "Produce component diagram, data flow, API contracts, and storage choices" ;
    oc:expectedOutcome "High-level architecture with component boundaries and data flow" ;
    oc:stepDependsOn _:ref_18639116ad011c59 ;
    oc:stepId "high-level-design" .

_:ref_18639116ad011c59 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "Gather functional requirements, non-functional requirements (scale, latency, availability, cost), and constraints (team size, timeline, tech stack)" ;
    oc:expectedOutcome "Clear requirements document with explicit assumptions" ;
    oc:stepId "requirements" .

_:ref_55f18a6de7667a97 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "Design data model, API endpoints (REST/GraphQL/gRPC), caching strategy, queue/event design, and error handling" ;
    oc:expectedOutcome "Detailed design with concrete data models and endpoint specifications" ;
    oc:stepDependsOn _:ref_0f50c8242135a50c ;
    oc:stepId "deep-dive" .

_:ref_c5fa100f6e25757d a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "Estimate load, choose scaling approach, plan failover/redundancy, and define monitoring/alerting" ;
    oc:expectedOutcome "Scaling strategy and reliability plan with concrete numbers" ;
    oc:stepDependsOn _:ref_55f18a6de7667a97 ;
    oc:stepId "scale-reliability" .

